Example \(\PageIndex{2}\) Using the triangle shown, evaluate cos(\(\alpha\)), sin(\(\alpha\)), cos(\( eta\)), and sin(\( eta\)), Solution \[	ext{cos}(\alpha) = \dfrac{	ext{adjacent to } \alpha}{	ext{hypotenuse}} = \dfrac{3}{5}
onumber\] \[	ext{sin}(\alpha) = \dfrac{	ext{opposite } \alpha}{	ext{hypotenuse}} = \dfrac{4}{5}
onumber\] \[	ext{cos}( eta) = \dfrac{	ext{adjacent to }  eta}{	ext{hypotenuse}} = \dfrac{4}{5}
onumber\] \[	ext{cos}( eta) = \dfrac{	ext{opposite }  eta}{	ext{hypotenuse}} = \dfrac{3}{5}
